request.description:
Get real-time route simulation data for a shipment. Returns route points, current position, and phase (TO_PICKUP or TO_DELIVERY). Admin or Driver.

**Example Response (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "shipmentId": "shipment-123",
    "driverId": "driver-789",
    "phase": "TO_PICKUP",
    "routePoints": [
      {
        "lat": 40.7128,
        "lng": -74.0060
      },
      {
        "lat": 40.7130,
        "lng": -74.0058
      },
      {
        "lat": 40.7132,
        "lng": -74.0056
      }
    ],
    "currentStep": 15,
    "totalSteps": 200,
    "pickupPoint": {
      "lat": 40.7580,
      "lng": -73.9855
    },
    "deliveryPoint": {
      "lat": 40.6782,
      "lng": -73.9442
    }
  }
}
```

Get paginated list of notifications for the authenticated user. Returns notifications array and total count. Ordered by creation date (newest first). All authenticated users.

**Example Response (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "notifications": [
      {
        "id": "notif-123",
        "userId": "user-456",
        "type": "SHIPMENT_ASSIGNED",
        "title": "New Shipment Assignment",
        "message": "You have been assigned to shipment shipment-123",
        "status": "UNREAD",
        "metadata": {
          "shipmentId": "shipment-123",
          "driverId": "driver-789"
        },
        "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
        "readAt": null
      },
      {
        "id": "notif-456",
        "userId": "user-456",
        "type": "SHIPMENT_APPROVED",
        "title": "Shipment Approved",
        "message": "Driver approved shipment shipment-123",
        "status": "READ",
        "metadata": {
          "shipmentId": "shipment-123",
          "driverId": "driver-789"
        },
        "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:35:00Z",
        "readAt": "2024-01-15T10:40:00Z"
      }
    ],
    "total": 25,
    "limit": 50,
    "offset": 0
  }
}
```

Get the count of unread notifications. Useful for displaying a badge or indicator. All authenticated users.

**Example Response (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "unreadCount": 5
  }
}
```

Mark all unread notifications for the authenticated user as read. All authenticated users.

**Example Response (200):**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "All notifications marked as read",
  "data": {
    "updatedCount": 5
  }
}
```

Check system health status (database, Redis, RabbitMQ). No authentication required.

**Example Response (200):**
```json
{
  "status": "healthy",
  "services": {
    "database": "connected",
    "redis": "connected",
    "rabbitmq": "connected"
  },
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T11:00:00Z"
}
```

**Example Response (503 - Unhealthy):**
```json
{
  "status": "unhealthy",
  "services": {
    "database": "connected",
    "redis": "disconnected",
    "rabbitmq": "connected"
  },
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T11:00:00Z"
}
```
